Subject: Re: [T2] heater box patch

On Sat, 9 Apr 2005, Chris wrote:

> Is there a substance good to "patch" heater boxes where the manifold goes into the box when it "loosens" up there?
> thanx.

On mine, I made a split ring from sheet metal, slipped it into the gap,
and brazed it in place.  This closes the gap and also makes a larger
bearing surface, preventing the problem from recurring.

George Lyle
